2013-09-24  rocky <rocky@gnu.org>

	* Makefile.am: For reasons I don't understand, "make dist" doesn't
	work because "make distdir" isn't done before "make dist" and "make
	distdir" creates directories like "command". I'm guessing automake
	changed things around. Adding a dependency like of "dist" on
	"distdir" fixes this, although this seems to be a workaround for
	what looks like an automake problem.

